<h2 id="image-example-1">Image example 1</h2>

<p>Here, I will embedd image from local assets which goes into <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">assets</code> directory in projectâ€™s <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">root</code> directory. Choose a specific image, related to particular post. I chose to name the image <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">test-page-image-1.jpg</code>, which I will embedd as:</p>

<div class="language-markdown highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="p">![</span><span class="nv">my alternate text</span><span class="p">](</span><span class="sx">/assets/test-page-image-1.jpg</span><span class="p">)</span>;
</code></pre></div></div>

<p><img src="/assets/test-page-image-1.jpg" alt="my alternate text" />;</p>

<p>Ofcourse, you can load images from web as well. Just point to image direct URL. For ex, here is one placeholder image:</p>

<div class="language-markdown highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="p">![</span><span class="nv">my alternate text</span><span class="p">](</span><span class="sx">http://lorempixel.com/400/200</span><span class="p">)</span>;
</code></pre></div></div>

<p><img src="http://lorempixel.com/400/200" alt="my alternate text" />;</p>

<p>One cool thing about this is the fact that images adapt themselves to the screen size of device. Try to resize your browser window and check for yourself, Have fun.</p>
